            <title>[THRIFT-1473] JSON context stack may be left in an incorrect state when an exception is thrown during read or write operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1473</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JSON context stack may be left in an incorrect state when an exception is thrown during read or write operations. This leads to further errors while writing/reading the NEXT message, because incorrect characters may be written or expected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
